-- Big 12 Secures $2.6 Billion Deal With ABC, Fox, ESPN Reports
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2012-09-07T04:01:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-07/big-12-secures-2-6-billion-deal-with-abc-fox-espn-reports.html
The  Big 12  Conference reached a
media rights agreement worth $2.6 billion over 13 years with
 Walt Disney Co. (DIS) ’s ABC and ESPN, and  News Corp. (NWSA) ’s Fox network,
 ESPN reported , citing unidentified people in the industry.  The Big 12 board will vote today on the deal, which will
run through the 2024-25 school year, ESPN said.  Football games will be shared between the Disney and News
Corp. units, while ABC and ESPN will broadcast men’s basketball.  The contract works out at an average of $200 million a year
and $20 million annually for each of the conference’s 10
schools, the broadcaster said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dex McLuskey in Dallas  at
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net . 